# @param {Integer[]} nums
# @param {Integer} k
# @return {Integer}
def maximum_score(nums, k)
    mod = 10**9 + 7
    max_score = 1

    # Function to get prime score
    def get_prime_score(x)
        prime_factors = 0
        for i in 2..Math.sqrt(x)
            if x % i == 0
                prime_factors += 1 while (x % i).zero?
                x /= i while (x % i).zero?
            end
        end
        prime_factors += 1 if x > 1
        prime_factors
    end

    # Array to hold numbers with their prime scores
    prime_scores = nums.map { |x| [x, get_prime_score(x)] }

    # Sorting the array based on prime score, then by number in descending order
    prime_scores.sort_by! { |x, score| [-score, -x] }

    # Selecting top k elements based on their prime score
    k.times do |i|
        max_score = (max_score * prime_scores[i][0]) % mod
    end

    max_score
end
